Class SavedGameModel.UnsupportedSGMOperationException

    Enclosing class:
    SavedGameModel

    public static class SavedGameModel.UnsupportedSGMOperationException
extends java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
    Details of why SavedGameModel.checkCanSave(SOCGame) or SavedGameModel.checkCanLoad(SOCGameOptionSet) or constructor can't save a game or load a model. Throwable.getMessage() will name the unsupported option/feature, ideally with an i18n key from "admin.savegame.cannot_save.*" but possibly as free-form text like "a unique resource type": Put a try-catch around your attempt to localize that key. Optional localization params are param1 and param2.
    Since:
    2.4.00
